\frac{1}{2} \vert a \vert^2
 \mathbb{E}( \text{re}( \sum_k a_k x_k )^2 ) =  \mathbb{E}( \text{im}( \sum_k a_k x_k )^2 ) = \frac{1}{2} \sum_k \vert a_k \vert^2 = \frac{1}{2} \vert a \vert^2
 \mathbb{E}( \text{re}(\sum_k a_k x_k ) \text{im}( \sum_m a_m x_m ) ) = \sum_{k} \mathbb{E} (\text{re}(a_k x_k ) \text{im}( a_k x_k ) ) = \sum_k ( \text{re}(a_k) \text{im}( a_k ) - \text{im}(a_k) \text{re}( a_k ) ) = 0
